fields.description:
I have an app that runs fine in the simulator. But when I try to build and run on a recognized device, nothing happens. the console is empty etc. It was only through trying to start it through the command line that i received the error that the WWDR certificate was missing (one was installed, but had expired).

It would be great to have an error message.
fields.summary: Can't run on iOS device without WWDR, but no error message is given.
fields.environment: Mac OS 10.11.3, xcode 7.2.1, appcelerator studio 4.4.0.201511241829, SDK 5.1.2GA
